    },
    {
      "id": "uoSsZDBeLT16FNFzuAoNo",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1281.7085485935124,
      "y": 196.60083627035988,
      "width": 2317.92,
      "height": 1129.89,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bi6",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 174324866,
      "version": 872,
      "versionNonce": 1421599134,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1781199487989,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Architecture of the distributed platform. Two main entities: Master and Worker\n\n  ---\n  Master Node\n\n  Request pipeline:\n  - REST API — entry point, exposes CRUD endpoints for services, nodes, pools. Delegates processing to other modules.\n  - Security — authentication middleware (JWT validation) and authorization (ACL role check). Intercepts every request before processing.\n  - Audit Logger — append-only log. Receives events from Security and other modules. Stored on master, queryable via API.\n\n  Scheduling pipeline:\n  - Scheduler — receives deploy requests from API. Filters nodes in the requested pool that have sufficient resources, passes the candidate list to LB.\n  - Load Balancer — pluggable interface with two implementations: LeastConnections (fewest running containers) and Weighted (score by available CPU/RAM). Returns a single node.\n  - Cluster State (Raft FSM) — source of truth. Finite State Machine replicated across 3 master nodes via Raft. Stores: nodes, services, containers, pools, users. On every write, the entry goes into the Raft log.\n\n  Cluster health:\n  - Heartbeat Receiver — listens for UDP multicast packets. Receives every 5s from each worker: total and used CPU and RAM, the node address and the container list. Updates Cluster State.\n  - Fault Tolerance — periodic tick, checks time.Now() - lastHeartbeat for each node. 15s → SUSPECT, 30s → DEAD. On DEAD, starts fresh containers on healthy nodes using the original service parameters (image, cpu, ram, envVars, ports, cmd).\n  - Leader Election (Raft) — hashicorp/raft in Go. 3 master nodes, quorum of 2. Leader processes writes, followers replicate. On crash, election timeout → RequestVote → new leader takes over.\n\n  ---\n  Worker Node\n\n  - Monitor — reads system metrics (CPU, RAM usage). Passes them to Agent.\n  - Node Agent — main process. Two goroutines: (1) 5s ticker sending heartbeats with metrics, (2) TCP server receiving commands from master.\n  - Docker Engine — Agent interacts via Docker SDK. ContainerCreate, ContainerStart, ContainerStop.\n\n  ---\n  Master <--> Worker\n\n  - Heartbeat, UDP multicast, every 5s. Fire-and-forget, no ACK expected.\n  - Synchronous commands from Scheduler to Agent: start/stop container. Only triggered on deploy, scale, or reschedule.\n\n  ---\n  Actors\n\n  Admin, Writer, Reader — 3 ACL roles. All connect to REST API via JWT. The difference is strictly in what actions the Security module permits:\n  - Admin: full CRUD on all resources\n  - Writer: CRUD on services, read on nodes/pools\n  - Reader: read-only on everything\n\n",
      "fontSize": 21.52162184980117,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Architecture of the distributed platform. Two main entities: Master and Worker\n\n  ---\n  Master Node\n\n  Request pipeline:\n  - REST API — entry point, exposes CRUD endpoints for services, nodes, pools. Delegates processing to other modules.\n  - Security — authentication middleware (JWT validation) and authorization (ACL role check). Intercepts every request before processing.\n  - Audit Logger — append-only log. Receives events from Security and other modules. Stored on master, queryable via API.\n\n  Scheduling pipeline:\n  - Scheduler — receives deploy requests from API. Filters nodes in the requested pool that have sufficient resources, passes the candidate list to LB.\n  - Load Balancer — pluggable interface with two implementations: LeastConnections (fewest running containers) and Weighted (score by available CPU/RAM). Returns a single node.\n  - Cluster State (Raft FSM) — source of truth. Finite State Machine replicated across 3 master nodes via Raft. Stores: nodes, services, containers, pools, users. On every write, the entry goes into the Raft log.\n\n  Cluster health:\n  - Heartbeat Receiver — listens for UDP multicast packets. Receives every 5s from each worker: total and used CPU and RAM, the node address and the container list. Updates Cluster State.\n  - Fault Tolerance — periodic tick, checks time.Now() - lastHeartbeat for each node. 15s → SUSPECT, 30s → DEAD. On DEAD, starts fresh containers on healthy nodes using the original service parameters (image, cpu, ram, envVars, ports, cmd).\n  - Leader Election (Raft) — hashicorp/raft in Go. 3 master nodes, quorum of 2. Leader processes writes, followers replicate. On crash, election timeout → RequestVote → new leader takes over.\n\n  ---\n  Worker Node\n\n  - Monitor — reads system metrics (CPU, RAM usage). Passes them to Agent.\n  - Node Agent — main process. Two goroutines: (1) 5s ticker sending heartbeats with metrics, (2) TCP server receiving commands from master.\n  - Docker Engine — Agent interacts via Docker SDK. ContainerCreate, ContainerStart, ContainerStop.\n\n  ---\n  Master <--> Worker\n\n  - Heartbeat, UDP multicast, every 5s. Fire-and-forget, no ACK expected.\n  - Synchronous commands from Scheduler to Agent: start/stop container. Only triggered on deploy, scale, or reschedule.\n\n  ---\n  Actors\n\n  Admin, Writer, Reader — 3 ACL roles. All connect to REST API via JWT. The difference is strictly in what actions the Security module permits:\n  - Admin: full CRUD on all resources\n  - Writer: CRUD on services, read on nodes/pools\n  - Reader: read-only on everything\n\n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "IcoL8PLSWkpr0GMvlpX19",
      "type": "arrow",
      "x": 528.0343347433562,
      "y": 3446.7901928767496,
      "width": 462.6845790214539,
      "height": 2.2912233258228873,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
