      "updated": 1781203020375,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": " Container State Machine \n\n  PENDING — the container needs to run, but the cluster cannot currently take it. A retry loop tries to schedule it again every 10 seconds; PENDING containers of the same service start only together (all-or-nothing). \n  SCHEDULED — a node was found. The container has been assigned to a worker and Docker startup is expected. This is a transient state — lasts a few seconds.\n  RUNNING — the container is actively running on a worker. Docker started it successfully. This is the normal state where the container spends most of its time.\n  FAILED — Docker returned an error at startup (invalid image, port conflict, out of memory). This is a final state.\n  RESCHEDULING — the container was running normally, but the node it was running on died. A fresh container needs to be started on another node. This is the intermediate state between detecting the node's death and finding a new node.\n  STOPPED — the container was stopped intentionally. The user deleted the service or reduced the replica count (scale down). This is a final state — the container doesn't come back.\n\n  Transitions\n\n  Happy path:\n  - Service was created, container enters the queue \n  - Node selected — Scheduler found a node with resources, Load Balancer picked the best one\n  - Docker started OK — Docker Engine on the worker started the container successfully\n  - Deleted or scaled down — user requested shutdown\n\n  Docker error flow:\n  - Docker error — Docker could not start the container; the container is marked FAILED\n\n  Recovery flow:\n  - No nodes available — recovery found no suitable node; the container returns to PENDING and the retry loop picks it up later.\n\n  Fault tolerance flow (node dies):\n  - Host node died — Fault Tolerance detected the node is DEAD (30s without heartbeat). The container needs to be moved.\n  - New node found — Scheduler found another available node, container is rescheduled\n\n  Connection to other diagrams\n\n  - Fault Tolerance triggers the RUNNING → RESCHEDULING transition\n  - Service Deployment triggers ● → PENDING → SCHEDULED → RUNNING\n  - Node States — when a node transitions to DEAD, its containers transition to RESCHEDULING\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": " Container State Machine \n\n  PENDING — the container needs to run, but the cluster cannot currently take it. A retry loop tries to schedule it again every 10 seconds; PENDING containers of the same service start only together (all-or-nothing). \n  SCHEDULED — a node was found. The container has been assigned to a worker and Docker startup is expected. This is a transient state — lasts a few seconds.\n  RUNNING — the container is actively running on a worker. Docker started it successfully. This is the normal state where the container spends most of its time.\n  FAILED — Docker returned an error at startup (invalid image, port conflict, out of memory). This is a final state.\n  RESCHEDULING — the container was running normally, but the node it was running on died. A fresh container needs to be started on another node. This is the intermediate state between detecting the node's death and finding a new node.\n  STOPPED — the container was stopped intentionally. The user deleted the service or reduced the replica count (scale down). This is a final state — the container doesn't come back.\n\n  Transitions\n\n  Happy path:\n  - Service was created, container enters the queue \n  - Node selected — Scheduler found a node with resources, Load Balancer picked the best one\n  - Docker started OK — Docker Engine on the worker started the container successfully\n  - Deleted or scaled down — user requested shutdown\n\n  Docker error flow:\n  - Docker error — Docker could not start the container; the container is marked FAILED\n\n  Recovery flow:\n  - No nodes available — recovery found no suitable node; the container returns to PENDING and the retry loop picks it up later.\n\n  Fault tolerance flow (node dies):\n  - Host node died — Fault Tolerance detected the node is DEAD (30s without heartbeat). The container needs to be moved.\n  - New node found — Scheduler found another available node, container is rescheduled\n\n  Connection to other diagrams\n\n  - Fault Tolerance triggers the RUNNING → RESCHEDULING transition\n  - Service Deployment triggers ● → PENDING → SCHEDULED → RUNNING\n  - Node States — when a node transitions to DEAD, its containers transition to RESCHEDULING\n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "g1c5gjIdJ5RfCpjxR6-zz",
