      "updated": 1781201954491,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": " Cluster Deployment Topology \n\n  Master Nodes — Raft Quorum (3 nodes)\n  - Master 1 (Leader) — the active master. Exposes two ports:\n    - API :8090 — the REST API where users connect (HTTP + JWT)\n    - HB :9090 — the UDP port listening for heartbeats from workers\n  - Master 2 (Follower) and Master 3 (Follower) — replicas that also expose the REST API (ports 8091, 8092). They do not make decisions; a write request sent to a follower is forwarded transparently to the leader, so users can use any master address. They still receive heartbeats, but only the leader acts on them, and they replicate state from the Leader via Raft.\n    Every decision by the leader (node added, container started, service created) is replicated to all followers.\n    Raft communication between masters uses plain TCP (trusted network).\n\n  Pool: high-cpu \n\n  A resource pool for workloads that need high processing power:\n\n  - Worker 1 (8 CPU / 16GB RAM) — runs SvcA — replica 1\n  - Worker 2 (8 CPU / 16GB RAM) — runs SvcB — replica 1\n\n  Both workers were automatically placed in this pool when their first heartbeat was received, because their CPU count (8) falls within the pool's range. \n  When someone deploys with pool: high-cpu, the Scheduler will only choose from these nodes.\n\n  Pool: high-ram\n\n  A pool for workloads that need a lot of memory:\n  - Worker 3 (4 CPU / 64GB RAM) — runs SvcC — replica 1\n\n  It has less CPU but 4 times more RAM than the high-cpu nodes. Ideal for in-memory databases, caches, or applications that process large datasets.\n\n  Each worker sends a heartbeat to the master every 5 seconds via UDP multicast. The heartbeat contains: total and used CPU and RAM, the node address and the container list.\n  The Admin actor connects to Master 1 (Leader) via HTTP + JWT. Sends requests to API :8090 — deploy services, view status, manage pools.\n\n \n",
      "fontSize": 22.24828765102888,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": " Cluster Deployment Topology \n\n  Master Nodes — Raft Quorum (3 nodes)\n  - Master 1 (Leader) — the active master. Exposes two ports:\n    - API :8090 — the REST API where users connect (HTTP + JWT)\n    - HB :9090 — the UDP port listening for heartbeats from workers\n  - Master 2 (Follower) and Master 3 (Follower) — replicas that also expose the REST API (ports 8091, 8092). They do not make decisions; a write request sent to a follower is forwarded transparently to the leader, so users can use any master address. They still receive heartbeats, but only the leader acts on them, and they replicate state from the Leader via Raft.\n    Every decision by the leader (node added, container started, service created) is replicated to all followers.\n    Raft communication between masters uses plain TCP (trusted network).\n\n  Pool: high-cpu \n\n  A resource pool for workloads that need high processing power:\n\n  - Worker 1 (8 CPU / 16GB RAM) — runs SvcA — replica 1\n  - Worker 2 (8 CPU / 16GB RAM) — runs SvcB — replica 1\n\n  Both workers were automatically placed in this pool when their first heartbeat was received, because their CPU count (8) falls within the pool's range. \n  When someone deploys with pool: high-cpu, the Scheduler will only choose from these nodes.\n\n  Pool: high-ram\n\n  A pool for workloads that need a lot of memory:\n  - Worker 3 (4 CPU / 64GB RAM) — runs SvcC — replica 1\n\n  It has less CPU but 4 times more RAM than the high-cpu nodes. Ideal for in-memory databases, caches, or applications that process large datasets.\n\n  Each worker sends a heartbeat to the master every 5 seconds via UDP multicast. The heartbeat contains: total and used CPU and RAM, the node address and the container list.\n  The Admin actor connects to Master 1 (Leader) via HTTP + JWT. Sends requests to API :8090 — deploy services, view status, manage pools.\n\n \n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "98KNeXzPogDaFea2cy7TJ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1332.9644260655846,
      "y": 9774.958829615869,
      "width": 3696.18,
      "height": 1200.0,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "dashed",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
